verbose_text: In the urban areas of SEA, the annual-mean air pollution levels are far exceeding the limits set by WHO (20 and 10 mug m -3 for PM 10 and PM 2.5, respectively) or the European Union standards of 50 and 25 mug m -3, respectively, by 5-10 times and being responsible for 30-45 deaths per 100,000 capita.
